### Footnotes

<span id="fn_1352"></span>[316:1](sbe24141.htm#fr_1363.md) The dedication
to the angel Bahirâm, which begins with these words (see Sîr. I. 20).

<span id="fn_1353"></span>[316:2](sbe24142.htm#fr_1364.md) A childless
widow who has married again, and half of whose children, by her second
husband, belong to her first one, to whom she also belongs in the other
world (see Bd. XXXII, 6 n).

<span id="fn_1354"></span>[316:3](sbe24142.htm#fr_1365.md) B29 has 'if a
male child be born.'

<span id="fn_1355"></span>[316:4](sbe24142.htm#fr_1366.md) The child being
considered to belong to its mother's first husband, can be only an
adopted son of her second husband.

<span id="fn_1356"></span>[316:5](sbe24142.htm#fr_1367.md) The *K*inva*d*
bridge, which is the passage to heaven.

